headline: KeyBanc upgrades DuPont to ’overweight’ amid lingering recession risk
summary: Investing.com -- KeyBanc Capital Markets warned of persistent macro headwinds for the U.S. chemicals sector in a first-quarter preview, cutting 2025 EBITDA estimates across the board by 5% on average and flagging a potential 28% median downside in a recession scenario. Even with this cautious stance, the firm upgraded DuPont (NYSE:DD) to “Overweight,” citing attractive valuation and resilient business segments.
